Extension: Cross-version Extension `R5.StructureMap.group.rule` for use in FHIR R4

0.0.1-snapshot-3
Official URL: http://hl7.org/fhir/5.0/StructureDefinition/extension-StructureMap.group.rule Version:
Standards status: Trial-use Active as of 2026-02-10 Maturity Level: 0 Computable Name: ExtensionStructureMap_Group_Rule

This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element StructureMap.group.rule for use in FHIR R4.

Context of Use

    This extension may be used on the following element(s)

    • Element ID: Extension.extension

    This extension is allowed for use with FHIR versions R4 to R4 .

Usage info

Usages:

  • This Extension is not used by any profiles in this Implementation Guide

You can also check for usages in the FHIR IG Statistics

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element StructureMap.group.rule for use in FHIR R4.

  • name: id: Name of the rule for internal references.
  • context: id: Type or variable this rule applies to.
  • min: integer: Specified minimum cardinality for the element. This is optional; if present, it acts an implicit check on the input content.
  • max: string: Specified maximum cardinality for the element - a number or a "". This is optional; if present, it acts an implicit check on the input content ( just serves as documentation; it's the default value).
  • type: string: Specified type for the element. This works as a condition on the mapping - use for polymorphic elements.
  • defaultValue: string: A value to use if there is no existing value in the source object.
  • element: string: Optional field for this source.
  • listMode: code: How to handle the list mode for this element.
  • variable: id: Named context for field, if a field is specified.
  • condition: string: FHIRPath expression - must be true or the rule does not apply.
  • check: string: FHIRPath expression - must be true or the mapping engine throws an error instead of completing.
  • logMessage: string: A FHIRPath expression which specifies a message to put in the transform log when content matching the source rule is found.
  • context: string: Variable this rule applies to.
  • element: string: Field to create in the context.
  • variable: id: Named context for field, if desired, and a field is specified.
  • listMode: code: If field is a list, how to manage the list.
  • listRuleId: id: Internal rule reference for shared list items.
  • transform: code: How the data is copied / created.
  • parameter: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: Parameters to the transform.
  • rule: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: Rules contained in this rule.
  • name: id: Name of a rule or group to apply.

Summary

Complex Extension: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element StructureMap.group.rule for use in FHIR R4.

  • name: id: Name of the rule for internal references.
  • context: id: Type or variable this rule applies to.
  • min: integer: Specified minimum cardinality for the element. This is optional; if present, it acts an implicit check on the input content.
  • max: string: Specified maximum cardinality for the element - a number or a "". This is optional; if present, it acts an implicit check on the input content ( just serves as documentation; it's the default value).
  • type: string: Specified type for the element. This works as a condition on the mapping - use for polymorphic elements.
  • defaultValue: string: A value to use if there is no existing value in the source object.
  • element: string: Optional field for this source.
  • listMode: code: How to handle the list mode for this element.
  • variable: id: Named context for field, if a field is specified.
  • condition: string: FHIRPath expression - must be true or the rule does not apply.
  • check: string: FHIRPath expression - must be true or the mapping engine throws an error instead of completing.
  • logMessage: string: A FHIRPath expression which specifies a message to put in the transform log when content matching the source rule is found.
  • context: string: Variable this rule applies to.
  • element: string: Field to create in the context.
  • variable: id: Named context for field, if desired, and a field is specified.
  • listMode: code: If field is a list, how to manage the list.
  • listRuleId: id: Internal rule reference for shared list items.
  • transform: code: How the data is copied / created.
  • parameter: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: Parameters to the transform.
  • rule: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: Rules contained in this rule.
  • name: id: Name of a rule or group to apply.
  • parameter: base64Binary, boolean, canonical, code, date, dateTime, decimal, id, instant, integer, markdown, oid, positiveInt, string, time, unsignedInt, uri, url, uuid, Address, Age, Annotation, Attachment, CodeableConcept, Coding, ContactPoint, Count, Distance, Duration, HumanName, Identifier, Money, Period, Quantity, Range, Ratio, Reference, SampledData, Signature, Timing, ContactDetail, Contributor, DataRequirement, Expression, ParameterDefinition, RelatedArtifact, TriggerDefinition, UsageContext, Dosage, Meta: Parameter to pass to the rule or group.
